50 Vec2d df, dc;
51 Vec4d dk;

59//////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
60/// cv::fisheye::projectPoints
61
62void cv::fisheye::projectPoints(InputArray objectPoints, OutputArray imagePoints, const Affine3d& affine,
63 InputArray K, InputArray D, double alpha, OutputArray jacobian)
64{
65 projectPoints(objectPoints, imagePoints, affine.rvec(), affine.translation(), K, D, alpha, jacobian);
66}
67
68void cv::fisheye::projectPoints(InputArray objectPoints, OutputArray imagePoints, InputArray _rvec,
69 InputArray _tvec, InputArray _K, InputArray _D, double alpha, OutputArray jacobian)
70{
71 // will support only 3-channel data now for points
72 CV_Assert(objectPoints.type() == CV_32FC3 || objectPoints.type() == CV_64FC3);
73 imagePoints.create(objectPoints.size(), CV_MAKETYPE(objectPoints.depth(), 2));
74 size_t n = objectPoints.total();
75
76 CV_Assert(_rvec.total() * _rvec.channels() == 3 && (_rvec.depth() == CV_32F || _rvec.depth() == CV_64F));
77 CV_Assert(_tvec.total() * _tvec.channels() == 3 && (_tvec.depth() == CV_32F || _tvec.depth() == CV_64F));
78 CV_Assert(_tvec.getMat().isContinuous() && _rvec.getMat().isContinuous());
79
80 Vec3d om = _rvec.depth() == CV_32F ? (Vec3d)*_rvec.getMat().ptr<Vec3f>() : *_rvec.getMat().ptr<Vec3d>();
81 Vec3d T = _tvec.depth() == CV_32F ? (Vec3d)*_tvec.getMat().ptr<Vec3f>() : *_tvec.getMat().ptr<Vec3d>();
82
83 CV_Assert(_K.size() == Size(3,3) && (_K.type() == CV_32F || _K.type() == CV_64F) && _D.type() == _K.type() && _D.total() == 4);
84
85 cv::Vec2d f, c;
86 if (_K.depth() == CV_32F)
87 {
88
89 Matx33f K = _K.getMat();
90 f = Vec2f(K(0, 0), K(1, 1));
91 c = Vec2f(K(0, 2), K(1, 2));
92 }
93 else
94 {
95 Matx33d K = _K.getMat();
96 f = Vec2d(K(0, 0), K(1, 1));
97 c = Vec2d(K(0, 2), K(1, 2));
98 }
99
100 Vec4d k = _D.depth() == CV_32F ? (Vec4d)*_D.getMat().ptr<Vec4f>(): *_D.getMat().ptr<Vec4d>();
101
102 JacobianRow *Jn = 0;
103 if (jacobian.needed())
104 {
105 int nvars = 2 + 2 + 1 + 4 + 3 + 3; // f, c, alpha, k, om, T,
106 jacobian.create(2*(int)n, nvars, CV_64F);
107 Jn = jacobian.getMat().ptr<JacobianRow>(0);
108 }
109
110 Matx33d R;
111 Matx<double, 3, 9> dRdom;
112 Rodrigues(om, R, dRdom);
113 Affine3d aff(om, T);
114
115 const Vec3f* Xf = objectPoints.getMat().ptr<Vec3f>();
116 const Vec3d* Xd = objectPoints.getMat().ptr<Vec3d>();
117 Vec2f *xpf = imagePoints.getMat().ptr<Vec2f>();
118 Vec2d *xpd = imagePoints.getMat().ptr<Vec2d>();
119
120 for(size_t i = 0; i < n; ++i)
121 {
122 Vec3d Xi = objectPoints.depth() == CV_32F ? (Vec3d)Xf[i] : Xd[i];
123 Vec3d Y = aff*Xi;
124
125 Vec2d x(Y[0]/Y[2], Y[1]/Y[2]);
126
127 double r2 = x.dot(x);
128 double r = std::sqrt(r2);
129
130 // Angle of the incoming ray:
131 double theta = atan(r);
132
133 double theta2 = theta*theta, theta3 = theta2*theta, theta4 = theta2*theta2, theta5 = theta4*theta,
134 theta6 = theta3*theta3, theta7 = theta6*theta, theta8 = theta4*theta4, theta9 = theta8*theta;
135
136 double theta_d = theta + k[0]*theta3 + k[1]*theta5 + k[2]*theta7 + k[3]*theta9;
137
138 double inv_r = r > 1e-8 ? 1.0/r : 1;
139 double cdist = r > 1e-8 ? theta_d * inv_r : 1;
140
141 Vec2d xd1 = x * cdist;
142 Vec2d xd3(xd1[0] + alpha*xd1[1], xd1[1]);
143 Vec2d final_point(xd3[0] * f[0] + c[0], xd3[1] * f[1] + c[1]);
144
145 if (objectPoints.depth() == CV_32F)
146 xpf[i] = final_point;
147 else
148 xpd[i] = final_point;
149
150 if (jacobian.needed())
151 {
152 //Vec3d Xi = pdepth == CV_32F ? (Vec3d)Xf[i] : Xd[i];
153 //Vec3d Y = aff*Xi;
154 double dYdR[] = { Xi[0], Xi[1], Xi[2], 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0,
155 0, 0, 0, Xi[0], Xi[1], Xi[2], 0, 0, 0,
156 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, Xi[0], Xi[1], Xi[2] };
157
158 Matx33d dYdom_data = Matx<double, 3, 9>(dYdR) * dRdom.t();
159 const Vec3d *dYdom = (Vec3d*)dYdom_data.val;
160
161 Matx33d dYdT_data = Matx33d::eye();
162 const Vec3d *dYdT = (Vec3d*)dYdT_data.val;
163
164 //Vec2d x(Y[0]/Y[2], Y[1]/Y[2]);
165 Vec3d dxdom[2];
166 dxdom[0] = (1.0/Y[2]) * dYdom[0] - x[0]/Y[2] * dYdom[2];
167 dxdom[1] = (1.0/Y[2]) * dYdom[1] - x[1]/Y[2] * dYdom[2];
168
169 Vec3d dxdT[2];
170 dxdT[0] = (1.0/Y[2]) * dYdT[0] - x[0]/Y[2] * dYdT[2];
171 dxdT[1] = (1.0/Y[2]) * dYdT[1] - x[1]/Y[2] * dYdT[2];
172
173 //double r2 = x.dot(x);
174 Vec3d dr2dom = 2 * x[0] * dxdom[0] + 2 * x[1] * dxdom[1];
175 Vec3d dr2dT = 2 * x[0] * dxdT[0] + 2 * x[1] * dxdT[1];
176
177 //double r = std::sqrt(r2);
178 double drdr2 = r > 1e-8 ? 1.0/(2*r) : 1;
179 Vec3d drdom = drdr2 * dr2dom;
180 Vec3d drdT = drdr2 * dr2dT;
181
182 // Angle of the incoming ray:
183 //double theta = atan(r);
184 double dthetadr = 1.0/(1+r2);
185 Vec3d dthetadom = dthetadr * drdom;
186 Vec3d dthetadT = dthetadr * drdT;
187
188 //double theta_d = theta + k[0]*theta3 + k[1]*theta5 + k[2]*theta7 + k[3]*theta9;
189 double dtheta_ddtheta = 1 + 3*k[0]*theta2 + 5*k[1]*theta4 + 7*k[2]*theta6 + 9*k[3]*theta8;
190 Vec3d dtheta_ddom = dtheta_ddtheta * dthetadom;
191 Vec3d dtheta_ddT = dtheta_ddtheta * dthetadT;
192 Vec4d dtheta_ddk = Vec4d(theta3, theta5, theta7, theta9);
193
194 //double inv_r = r > 1e-8 ? 1.0/r : 1;
195 //double cdist = r > 1e-8 ? theta_d / r : 1;
196 Vec3d dcdistdom = inv_r * (dtheta_ddom - cdist*drdom);
197 Vec3d dcdistdT = inv_r * (dtheta_ddT - cdist*drdT);
198 Vec4d dcdistdk = inv_r * dtheta_ddk;
199
200 //Vec2d xd1 = x * cdist;
201 Vec4d dxd1dk[2];
202 Vec3d dxd1dom[2], dxd1dT[2];
203 dxd1dom[0] = x[0] * dcdistdom + cdist * dxdom[0];
204 dxd1dom[1] = x[1] * dcdistdom + cdist * dxdom[1];
205 dxd1dT[0] = x[0] * dcdistdT + cdist * dxdT[0];
206 dxd1dT[1] = x[1] * dcdistdT + cdist * dxdT[1];
207 dxd1dk[0] = x[0] * dcdistdk;
208 dxd1dk[1] = x[1] * dcdistdk;
209
210 //Vec2d xd3(xd1[0] + alpha*xd1[1], xd1[1]);
211 Vec4d dxd3dk[2];
212 Vec3d dxd3dom[2], dxd3dT[2];
213 dxd3dom[0] = dxd1dom[0] + alpha * dxd1dom[1];
214 dxd3dom[1] = dxd1dom[1];
215 dxd3dT[0] = dxd1dT[0] + alpha * dxd1dT[1];
216 dxd3dT[1] = dxd1dT[1];
217 dxd3dk[0] = dxd1dk[0] + alpha * dxd1dk[1];
218 dxd3dk[1] = dxd1dk[1];
219
220 Vec2d dxd3dalpha(xd1[1], 0);
221
222 //final jacobian
223 Jn[0].dom = f[0] * dxd3dom[0];
224 Jn[1].dom = f[1] * dxd3dom[1];
225
226 Jn[0].dT = f[0] * dxd3dT[0];
227 Jn[1].dT = f[1] * dxd3dT[1];
228
229 Jn[0].dk = f[0] * dxd3dk[0];
230 Jn[1].dk = f[1] * dxd3dk[1];
231
232 Jn[0].dalpha = f[0] * dxd3dalpha[0];
233 Jn[1].dalpha = 0; //f[1] * dxd3dalpha[1];
234
235 Jn[0].df = Vec2d(xd3[0], 0);
236 Jn[1].df = Vec2d(0, xd3[1]);
237
238 Jn[0].dc = Vec2d(1, 0);
239 Jn[1].dc = Vec2d(0, 1);
240
241 //step to jacobian rows for next point
242 Jn += 2;
243 }
244 }
245}

247//////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
248/// cv::fisheye::distortPoints
249
250void cv::fisheye::distortPoints(InputArray undistorted, OutputArray distorted, InputArray K, InputArray D, double alpha)
251{
252 // will support only 2-channel data now for points
253 CV_Assert(undistorted.type() == CV_32FC2 || undistorted.type() == CV_64FC2);
254 distorted.create(undistorted.size(), undistorted.type());
255 size_t n = undistorted.total();
256
257 CV_Assert(K.size() == Size(3,3) && (K.type() == CV_32F || K.type() == CV_64F) && D.total() == 4);
258
259 cv::Vec2d f, c;
260 if (K.depth() == CV_32F)
261 {
262 Matx33f camMat = K.getMat();
263 f = Vec2f(camMat(0, 0), camMat(1, 1));
264 c = Vec2f(camMat(0, 2), camMat(1, 2));
265 }
266 else
267 {
268 Matx33d camMat = K.getMat();
269 f = Vec2d(camMat(0, 0), camMat(1, 1));
270 c = Vec2d(camMat(0 ,2), camMat(1, 2));
271 }
272
273 Vec4d k = D.depth() == CV_32F ? (Vec4d)*D.getMat().ptr<Vec4f>(): *D.getMat().ptr<Vec4d>();
274
275 const Vec2f* Xf = undistorted.getMat().ptr<Vec2f>();
276 const Vec2d* Xd = undistorted.getMat().ptr<Vec2d>();
277 Vec2f *xpf = distorted.getMat().ptr<Vec2f>();
278 Vec2d *xpd = distorted.getMat().ptr<Vec2d>();
279
280 for(size_t i = 0; i < n; ++i)
281 {
282 Vec2d x = undistorted.depth() == CV_32F ? (Vec2d)Xf[i] : Xd[i];
283
284 double r2 = x.dot(x);
285 double r = std::sqrt(r2);
286
287 // Angle of the incoming ray:
288 double theta = atan(r);
289
290 double theta2 = theta*theta, theta3 = theta2*theta, theta4 = theta2*theta2, theta5 = theta4*theta,
291 theta6 = theta3*theta3, theta7 = theta6*theta, theta8 = theta4*theta4, theta9 = theta8*theta;
292
293 double theta_d = theta + k[0]*theta3 + k[1]*theta5 + k[2]*theta7 + k[3]*theta9;
294
295 double inv_r = r > 1e-8 ? 1.0/r : 1;
296 double cdist = r > 1e-8 ? theta_d * inv_r : 1;
297
298 Vec2d xd1 = x * cdist;
299 Vec2d xd3(xd1[0] + alpha*xd1[1], xd1[1]);
300 Vec2d final_point(xd3[0] * f[0] + c[0], xd3[1] * f[1] + c[1]);
301
302 if (undistorted.depth() == CV_32F)
303 xpf[i] = final_point;
304 else
305 xpd[i] = final_point;
306 }
307}

309//////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
310/// cv::fisheye::undistortPoints
311
312void cv::fisheye::undistortPoints( InputArray distorted, OutputArray undistorted, InputArray K, InputArray D, InputArray R, InputArray P)
313{
314 // will support only 2-channel data now for points
315 CV_Assert(distorted.type() == CV_32FC2 || distorted.type() == CV_64FC2);
316 undistorted.create(distorted.size(), distorted.type());
317
318 CV_Assert(P.empty() || P.size() == Size(3, 3) || P.size() == Size(4, 3));
319 CV_Assert(R.empty() || R.size() == Size(3, 3) || R.total() * R.channels() == 3);
320 CV_Assert(D.total() == 4 && K.size() == Size(3, 3) && (K.depth() == CV_32F || K.depth() == CV_64F));
321
322 cv::Vec2d f, c;
323 if (K.depth() == CV_32F)
324 {
325 Matx33f camMat = K.getMat();
326 f = Vec2f(camMat(0, 0), camMat(1, 1));
327 c = Vec2f(camMat(0, 2), camMat(1, 2));
328 }
329 else
330 {
331 Matx33d camMat = K.getMat();
332 f = Vec2d(camMat(0, 0), camMat(1, 1));
333 c = Vec2d(camMat(0, 2), camMat(1, 2));
334 }
335
336 Vec4d k = D.depth() == CV_32F ? (Vec4d)*D.getMat().ptr<Vec4f>(): *D.getMat().ptr<Vec4d>();
337
338 cv::Matx33d RR = cv::Matx33d::eye();
339 if (!R.empty() && R.total() * R.channels() == 3)
340 {
341 cv::Vec3d rvec;
342 R.getMat().convertTo(rvec, CV_64F);
343 RR = cv::Affine3d(rvec).rotation();
344 }
345 else if (!R.empty() && R.size() == Size(3, 3))
346 R.getMat().convertTo(RR, CV_64F);
347
348 if(!P.empty())
349 {
350 cv::Matx33d PP;
351 P.getMat().colRange(0, 3).convertTo(PP, CV_64F);
352 RR = PP * RR;
353 }
354
355 // start undistorting
356 const cv::Vec2f* srcf = distorted.getMat().ptr<cv::Vec2f>();
357 const cv::Vec2d* srcd = distorted.getMat().ptr<cv::Vec2d>();
358 cv::Vec2f* dstf = undistorted.getMat().ptr<cv::Vec2f>();
359 cv::Vec2d* dstd = undistorted.getMat().ptr<cv::Vec2d>();
360
361 size_t n = distorted.total();
362 int sdepth = distorted.depth();
363
364 for(size_t i = 0; i < n; i++ )
365 {
366 Vec2d pi = sdepth == CV_32F ? (Vec2d)srcf[i] : srcd[i]; // image point
367 Vec2d pw((pi[0] - c[0])/f[0], (pi[1] - c[1])/f[1]); // world point
368
369 double scale = 1.0;
370
371 double theta_d = sqrt(pw[0]*pw[0] + pw[1]*pw[1]);
372
373 // the current camera model is only valid up to 180° FOV
374 // for larger FOV the loop below does not converge
375 // clip values so we still get plausible results for super fisheye images > 180°
376 theta_d = min(max(-CV_PI/2., theta_d), CV_PI/2.);
377
378 if (theta_d > 1e-8)
379 {
380 // compensate distortion iteratively
381 double theta = theta_d;
382 for(int j = 0; j < 10; j++ )
383 {
384 double theta2 = theta*theta, theta4 = theta2*theta2, theta6 = theta4*theta2, theta8 = theta6*theta2;
385 theta = theta_d / (1 + k[0] * theta2 + k[1] * theta4 + k[2] * theta6 + k[3] * theta8);
386 }
387
388 scale = std::tan(theta) / theta_d;
389 }
390
391 Vec2d pu = pw * scale; //undistorted point
392
393 // reproject
394 Vec3d pr = RR * Vec3d(pu[0], pu[1], 1.0); // rotated point optionally multiplied by new camera matrix
395 Vec2d fi(pr[0]/pr[2], pr[1]/pr[2]); // final
396
397 if( sdepth == CV_32F )
398 dstf[i] = fi;
399 else
400 dstd[i] = fi;
401 }
402}

404//////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
405/// cv::fisheye::undistortPoints
406
407void cv::fisheye::initUndistortRectifyMap( InputArray K, InputArray D, InputArray R, InputArray P,
408 const cv::Size& size, int m1type, OutputArray map1, OutputArray map2 )
409{
410 CV_Assert( m1type == CV_16SC2 || m1type == CV_32F || m1type <=0 );
411 map1.create( size, m1type <= 0 ? CV_16SC2 : m1type );
412 map2.create( size, map1.type() == CV_16SC2 ? CV_16UC1 : CV_32F );
413
414 CV_Assert((K.depth() == CV_32F || K.depth() == CV_64F) && (D.depth() == CV_32F || D.depth() == CV_64F));
415 CV_Assert((P.depth() == CV_32F || P.depth() == CV_64F) && (R.depth() == CV_32F || R.depth() == CV_64F));
416 CV_Assert(K.size() == Size(3, 3) && (D.empty() || D.total() == 4));
417 CV_Assert(R.empty() || R.size() == Size(3, 3) || R.total() * R.channels() == 3);
418 CV_Assert(P.empty() || P.size() == Size(3, 3) || P.size() == Size(4, 3));
419
420 cv::Vec2d f, c;
421 if (K.depth() == CV_32F)
422 {
423 Matx33f camMat = K.getMat();
424 f = Vec2f(camMat(0, 0), camMat(1, 1));
425 c = Vec2f(camMat(0, 2), camMat(1, 2));
426 }
427 else
428 {
429 Matx33d camMat = K.getMat();
430 f = Vec2d(camMat(0, 0), camMat(1, 1));
431 c = Vec2d(camMat(0, 2), camMat(1, 2));
432 }
433
434 Vec4d k = Vec4d::all(0);
435 if (!D.empty())
436 k = D.depth() == CV_32F ? (Vec4d)*D.getMat().ptr<Vec4f>(): *D.getMat().ptr<Vec4d>();
437
438 cv::Matx33d RR = cv::Matx33d::eye();
439 if (!R.empty() && R.total() * R.channels() == 3)
440 {
441 cv::Vec3d rvec;
442 R.getMat().convertTo(rvec, CV_64F);
443 RR = Affine3d(rvec).rotation();
444 }
445 else if (!R.empty() && R.size() == Size(3, 3))
446 R.getMat().convertTo(RR, CV_64F);
447
448 cv::Matx33d PP = cv::Matx33d::eye();
449 if (!P.empty())
450 P.getMat().colRange(0, 3).convertTo(PP, CV_64F);
451
452 cv::Matx33d iR = (PP * RR).inv(cv::DECOMP_SVD);
453
454 for( int i = 0; i < size.height; ++i)
455 {
456 float* m1f = map1.getMat().ptr<float>(i);
457 float* m2f = map2.getMat().ptr<float>(i);
458 short* m1 = (short*)m1f;
459 ushort* m2 = (ushort*)m2f;
460
461 double _x = i*iR(0, 1) + iR(0, 2),
462 _y = i*iR(1, 1) + iR(1, 2),
463 _w = i*iR(2, 1) + iR(2, 2);
464
465 for( int j = 0; j < size.width; ++j)
466 {
467 double x = _x/_w, y = _y/_w;
468
469 double r = sqrt(x*x + y*y);
470 double theta = atan(r);
471
472 double theta2 = theta*theta, theta4 = theta2*theta2, theta6 = theta4*theta2, theta8 = theta4*theta4;
473 double theta_d = theta * (1 + k[0]*theta2 + k[1]*theta4 + k[2]*theta6 + k[3]*theta8);
474
475 double scale = (r == 0) ? 1.0 : theta_d / r;
476 double u = f[0]*x*scale + c[0];
477 double v = f[1]*y*scale + c[1];
478
479 if( m1type == CV_16SC2 )
480 {
481 int iu = cv::saturate_cast<int>(u*cv::INTER_TAB_SIZE);
482 int iv = cv::saturate_cast<int>(v*cv::INTER_TAB_SIZE);
483 m1[j*2+0] = (short)(iu >> cv::INTER_BITS);
484 m1[j*2+1] = (short)(iv >> cv::INTER_BITS);
485 m2[j] = (ushort)((iv & (cv::INTER_TAB_SIZE-1))*cv::INTER_TAB_SIZE + (iu & (cv::INTER_TAB_SIZE-1)));
486 }
487 else if( m1type == CV_32FC1 )
488 {
489 m1f[j] = (float)u;
490 m2f[j] = (float)v;
491 }
492
493 _x += iR(0, 0);
494 _y += iR(1, 0);
495 _w += iR(2, 0);
496 }
497 }
498}

500//////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
501/// cv::fisheye::undistortImage
502
503void cv::fisheye::undistortImage(InputArray distorted, OutputArray undistorted,
504 InputArray K, InputArray D, InputArray Knew, const Size& new_size)
505{
506 Size size = new_size.area() != 0 ? new_size : distorted.size();
507
508 cv::Mat map1, map2;
509 fisheye::initUndistortRectifyMap(K, D, cv::Matx33d::eye(), Knew, size, CV_16SC2, map1, map2 );
510 cv::remap(distorted, undistorted, map1, map2, INTER_LINEAR, BORDER_CONSTANT);
511}

514//////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
515/// cv::fisheye::estimateNewCameraMatrixForUndistortRectify
516
517void cv::fisheye::estimateNewCameraMatrixForUndistortRectify(InputArray K, InputArray D, const Size &image_size, InputArray R,
518 OutputArray P, double balance, const Size& new_size, double fov_scale)
519{
520 CV_Assert( K.size() == Size(3, 3) && (K.depth() == CV_32F || K.depth() == CV_64F));
521 CV_Assert((D.empty() || D.total() == 4) && (D.depth() == CV_32F || D.depth() == CV_64F || D.empty()));
522
523 int w = image_size.width, h = image_size.height;
524 balance = std::min(std::max(balance, 0.0), 1.0);
525
526 cv::Mat points(1, 4, CV_64FC2);
527 Vec2d* pptr = points.ptr<Vec2d>();
528 pptr[0] = Vec2d(w/2, 0);
529 pptr[1] = Vec2d(w, h/2);
530 pptr[2] = Vec2d(w/2, h);
531 pptr[3] = Vec2d(0, h/2);
532
533#if 0
534 const int N = 10;
535 cv::Mat points(1, N * 4, CV_64FC2);
536 Vec2d* pptr = points.ptr<Vec2d>();
537 for(int i = 0, k = 0; i < 10; ++i)
538 {
539 pptr[k++] = Vec2d(w/2, 0) - Vec2d(w/8, 0) + Vec2d(w/4/N*i, 0);
540 pptr[k++] = Vec2d(w/2, h-1) - Vec2d(w/8, h-1) + Vec2d(w/4/N*i, h-1);
541
542 pptr[k++] = Vec2d(0, h/2) - Vec2d(0, h/8) + Vec2d(0, h/4/N*i);
543 pptr[k++] = Vec2d(w-1, h/2) - Vec2d(w-1, h/8) + Vec2d(w-1, h/4/N*i);
544 }
545#endif
546
547 fisheye::undistortPoints(points, points, K, D, R);
548 cv::Scalar center_mass = mean(points);
549 cv::Vec2d cn(center_mass.val);
550
551 double aspect_ratio = (K.depth() == CV_32F) ? K.getMat().at<float >(0,0)/K.getMat().at<float> (1,1)
552 : K.getMat().at<double>(0,0)/K.getMat().at<double>(1,1);
553
554 // convert to identity ratio
555 cn[0] *= aspect_ratio;
556 for(size_t i = 0; i < points.total(); ++i)
557 pptr[i][1] *= aspect_ratio;
558
559 double minx = DBL_MAX, miny = DBL_MAX, maxx = -DBL_MAX, maxy = -DBL_MAX;
560 for(size_t i = 0; i < points.total(); ++i)
561 {
562 miny = std::min(miny, pptr[i][1]);
563 maxy = std::max(maxy, pptr[i][1]);
564 minx = std::min(minx, pptr[i][0]);
565 maxx = std::max(maxx, pptr[i][0]);
566 }
567
568#if 0
569 double minx = -DBL_MAX, miny = -DBL_MAX, maxx = DBL_MAX, maxy = DBL_MAX;
570 for(size_t i = 0; i < points.total(); ++i)
571 {
572 if (i % 4 == 0) miny = std::max(miny, pptr[i][1]);
573 if (i % 4 == 1) maxy = std::min(maxy, pptr[i][1]);
574 if (i % 4 == 2) minx = std::max(minx, pptr[i][0]);
575 if (i % 4 == 3) maxx = std::min(maxx, pptr[i][0]);
576 }
577#endif
578
579 double f1 = w * 0.5/(cn[0] - minx);
580 double f2 = w * 0.5/(maxx - cn[0]);
581 double f3 = h * 0.5 * aspect_ratio/(cn[1] - miny);
582 double f4 = h * 0.5 * aspect_ratio/(maxy - cn[1]);
583
584 double fmin = std::min(f1, std::min(f2, std::min(f3, f4)));
585 double fmax = std::max(f1, std::max(f2, std::max(f3, f4)));
586
587 double f = balance * fmin + (1.0 - balance) * fmax;
588 f *= fov_scale > 0 ? 1.0/fov_scale : 1.0;
589
590 cv::Vec2d new_f(f, f), new_c = -cn * f + Vec2d(w, h * aspect_ratio) * 0.5;
591
592 // restore aspect ratio
593 new_f[1] /= aspect_ratio;
594 new_c[1] /= aspect_ratio;
595
596 if (new_size.area() > 0)
597 {
598 double rx = new_size.width /(double)image_size.width;
599 double ry = new_size.height/(double)image_size.height;
600
601 new_f[0] *= rx; new_f[1] *= ry;
602 new_c[0] *= rx; new_c[1] *= ry;
603 }
604
605 Mat(Matx33d(new_f[0], 0, new_c[0],
606 0, new_f[1], new_c[1],
607 0, 0, 1)).convertTo(P, P.empty() ? K.type() : P.type());
608}

611//////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
612/// cv::fisheye::stereoRectify
613
614void cv::fisheye::stereoRectify( InputArray K1, InputArray D1, InputArray K2, InputArray D2, const Size& imageSize,
615 InputArray _R, InputArray _tvec, OutputArray R1, OutputArray R2, OutputArray P1, OutputArray P2,
616 OutputArray Q, int flags, const Size& newImageSize, double balance, double fov_scale)
617{
618 CV_Assert((_R.size() == Size(3, 3) || _R.total() * _R.channels() == 3) && (_R.depth() == CV_32F || _R.depth() == CV_64F));
619 CV_Assert(_tvec.total() * _tvec.channels() == 3 && (_tvec.depth() == CV_32F || _tvec.depth() == CV_64F));
620
621
622 cv::Mat aaa = _tvec.getMat().reshape(3, 1);
623
624 Vec3d rvec; // Rodrigues vector
625 if (_R.size() == Size(3, 3))
626 {
627 cv::Matx33d rmat;
628 _R.getMat().convertTo(rmat, CV_64F);
629 rvec = Affine3d(rmat).rvec();
630 }
631 else if (_R.total() * _R.channels() == 3)
632 _R.getMat().convertTo(rvec, CV_64F);
633
634 Vec3d tvec;
635 _tvec.getMat().convertTo(tvec, CV_64F);
636
637 // rectification algorithm
638 rvec *= -0.5; // get average rotation
639
640 Matx33d r_r;
641 Rodrigues(rvec, r_r); // rotate cameras to same orientation by averaging
642
643 Vec3d t = r_r * tvec;
644 Vec3d uu(t[0] > 0 ? 1 : -1, 0, 0);
645
646 // calculate global Z rotation
647 Vec3d ww = t.cross(uu);
648 double nw = norm(ww);
649 if (nw > 0.0)
650 ww *= acos(fabs(t[0])/cv::norm(t))/nw;
651
652 Matx33d wr;
653 Rodrigues(ww, wr);
654
655 // apply to both views
656 Matx33d ri1 = wr * r_r.t();
657 Mat(ri1, false).convertTo(R1, R1.empty() ? CV_64F : R1.type());
658 Matx33d ri2 = wr * r_r;
659 Mat(ri2, false).convertTo(R2, R2.empty() ? CV_64F : R2.type());
660 Vec3d tnew = ri2 * tvec;
661
662 // calculate projection/camera matrices. these contain the relevant rectified image internal params (fx, fy=fx, cx, cy)
663 Matx33d newK1, newK2;
664 estimateNewCameraMatrixForUndistortRectify(K1, D1, imageSize, R1, newK1, balance, newImageSize, fov_scale);
665 estimateNewCameraMatrixForUndistortRectify(K2, D2, imageSize, R2, newK2, balance, newImageSize, fov_scale);
666
667 double fc_new = std::min(newK1(1,1), newK2(1,1));
668 Point2d cc_new[2] = { Vec2d(newK1(0, 2), newK1(1, 2)), Vec2d(newK2(0, 2), newK2(1, 2)) };
669
670 // Vertical focal length must be the same for both images to keep the epipolar constraint use fy for fx also.
671 // For simplicity, set the principal points for both cameras to be the average
672 // of the two principal points (either one of or both x- and y- coordinates)
673 if( flags & cv::CALIB_ZERO_DISPARITY )
674 cc_new[0] = cc_new[1] = (cc_new[0] + cc_new[1]) * 0.5;
675 else
676 cc_new[0].y = cc_new[1].y = (cc_new[0].y + cc_new[1].y)*0.5;
677
678 Mat(Matx34d(fc_new, 0, cc_new[0].x, 0,
679 0, fc_new, cc_new[0].y, 0,
680 0, 0, 1, 0), false).convertTo(P1, P1.empty() ? CV_64F : P1.type());
681
682 Mat(Matx34d(fc_new, 0, cc_new[1].x, tnew[0]*fc_new, // baseline * focal length;,
683 0, fc_new, cc_new[1].y, 0,
684 0, 0, 1, 0), false).convertTo(P2, P2.empty() ? CV_64F : P2.type());
685
686 if (Q.needed())
687 Mat(Matx44d(1, 0, 0, -cc_new[0].x,
688 0, 1, 0, -cc_new[0].y,
689 0, 0, 0, fc_new,
690 0, 0, -1./tnew[0], (cc_new[0].x - cc_new[1].x)/tnew[0]), false).convertTo(Q, Q.empty() ? CV_64F : Q.depth());
691}
692
693//////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
694/// cv::fisheye::calibrate
695
696double cv::fisheye::calibrate(InputArrayOfArrays objectPoints, InputArrayOfArrays imagePoints, const Size& image_size,
697 InputOutputArray K, InputOutputArray D, OutputArrayOfArrays rvecs, OutputArrayOfArrays tvecs,
698 int flags , cv::TermCriteria criteria)
699{
700 CV_Assert(!objectPoints.empty() && !imagePoints.empty() && objectPoints.total() == imagePoints.total());
701 CV_Assert(objectPoints.type() == CV_32FC3 || objectPoints.type() == CV_64FC3);
702 CV_Assert(imagePoints.type() == CV_32FC2 || imagePoints.type() == CV_64FC2);
703 CV_Assert((!K.empty() && K.size() == Size(3,3)) || K.empty());
704 CV_Assert((!D.empty() && D.total() == 4) || D.empty());
705 CV_Assert((!rvecs.empty() && rvecs.channels() == 3) || rvecs.empty());
706 CV_Assert((!tvecs.empty() && tvecs.channels() == 3) || tvecs.empty());
707
708 CV_Assert(((flags & CALIB_USE_INTRINSIC_GUESS) && !K.empty() && !D.empty()) || !(flags & CALIB_USE_INTRINSIC_GUESS));
709
710 using namespace cv::internal;
711 //-------------------------------Initialization
712 IntrinsicParams finalParam;
713 IntrinsicParams currentParam;
714 IntrinsicParams errors;
715
716 finalParam.isEstimate[0] = 1;
717 finalParam.isEstimate[1] = 1;
718 finalParam.isEstimate[2] = 1;
719 finalParam.isEstimate[3] = 1;
720 finalParam.isEstimate[4] = flags & CALIB_FIX_SKEW ? 0 : 1;
721 finalParam.isEstimate[5] = flags & CALIB_FIX_K1 ? 0 : 1;
722 finalParam.isEstimate[6] = flags & CALIB_FIX_K2 ? 0 : 1;
723 finalParam.isEstimate[7] = flags & CALIB_FIX_K3 ? 0 : 1;
724 finalParam.isEstimate[8] = flags & CALIB_FIX_K4 ? 0 : 1;
725
726 const int recompute_extrinsic = flags & CALIB_RECOMPUTE_EXTRINSIC ? 1: 0;
727 const int check_cond = flags & CALIB_CHECK_COND ? 1 : 0;
728
729 const double alpha_smooth = 0.4;
730 const double thresh_cond = 1e6;
731 double change = 1;
732 Vec2d err_std;
733
734 Matx33d _K;
735 Vec4d _D;
736 if (flags & CALIB_USE_INTRINSIC_GUESS)
737 {
738 K.getMat().convertTo(_K, CV_64FC1);
739 D.getMat().convertTo(_D, CV_64FC1);
740 finalParam.Init(Vec2d(_K(0,0), _K(1, 1)),
741 Vec2d(_K(0,2), _K(1, 2)),
742 Vec4d(flags & CALIB_FIX_K1 ? 0 : _D[0],
743 flags & CALIB_FIX_K2 ? 0 : _D[1],
744 flags & CALIB_FIX_K3 ? 0 : _D[2],
745 flags & CALIB_FIX_K4 ? 0 : _D[3]),
746 _K(0, 1) / _K(0, 0));
747 }
748 else
749 {
750 finalParam.Init(Vec2d(max(image_size.width, image_size.height) / CV_PI, max(image_size.width, image_size.height) / CV_PI),
751 Vec2d(image_size.width / 2.0 - 0.5, image_size.height / 2.0 - 0.5));
752 }
753
754 errors.isEstimate = finalParam.isEstimate;
755
756 std::vector<Vec3d> omc(objectPoints.total()), Tc(objectPoints.total());
757
758 CalibrateExtrinsics(objectPoints, imagePoints, finalParam, check_cond, thresh_cond, omc, Tc);
759
760
761 //-------------------------------Optimization
762 for(int iter = 0; ; ++iter)
763 {
764 if ((criteria.type == 1 && iter >= criteria.maxCount) ||
765 (criteria.type == 2 && change <= criteria.epsilon) ||
766 (criteria.type == 3 && (change <= criteria.epsilon || iter >= criteria.maxCount)))
767 break;
768
769 double alpha_smooth2 = 1 - std::pow(1 - alpha_smooth, iter + 1.0);
770
771 Mat JJ2_inv, ex3;
772 ComputeJacobians(objectPoints, imagePoints, finalParam, omc, Tc, check_cond,thresh_cond, JJ2_inv, ex3);
773
774 Mat G = alpha_smooth2 * JJ2_inv * ex3;
775
776 currentParam = finalParam + G;
777
778 change = norm(Vec4d(currentParam.f[0], currentParam.f[1], currentParam.c[0], currentParam.c[1]) -
779 Vec4d(finalParam.f[0], finalParam.f[1], finalParam.c[0], finalParam.c[1]))
780 / norm(Vec4d(currentParam.f[0], currentParam.f[1], currentParam.c[0], currentParam.c[1]));
781
782 finalParam = currentParam;
783
784 if (recompute_extrinsic)
785 {
786 CalibrateExtrinsics(objectPoints, imagePoints, finalParam, check_cond,
787 thresh_cond, omc, Tc);
788 }
789 }
790
791 //-------------------------------Validation
792 double rms;
793 EstimateUncertainties(objectPoints, imagePoints, finalParam, omc, Tc, errors, err_std, thresh_cond,
794 check_cond, rms);
795
796 //-------------------------------
797 _K = Matx33d(finalParam.f[0], finalParam.f[0] * finalParam.alpha, finalParam.c[0],
798 0, finalParam.f[1], finalParam.c[1],
799 0, 0, 1);
800
801 if (K.needed()) cv::Mat(_K).convertTo(K, K.empty() ? CV_64FC1 : K.type());
802 if (D.needed()) cv::Mat(finalParam.k).convertTo(D, D.empty() ? CV_64FC1 : D.type());
803
804 if (rvecs.needed())
805 {
806 if( rvecs.kind() == _InputArray::STD_VECTOR_MAT )
807 {
808 rvecs.create((int)objectPoints.total(), 1, CV_64FC3);
809 for( int i = 0; i < (int)objectPoints.total(); i++ )
810 {
811 rvecs.create(3, 1, CV_64F, i, true);
812 Mat rv = rvecs.getMat(i);
813 *rv.ptr<Vec3d>(0) = omc[i];
814 }
815 }
816 else
817 {
818 cv::Mat(omc).convertTo(rvecs, rvecs.fixedType() ? rvecs.type() : CV_64FC3);
819 }
820 }
821
822 if (tvecs.needed())
823 {
824 if( tvecs.kind() == _InputArray::STD_VECTOR_MAT )
825 {
826 tvecs.create((int)objectPoints.total(), 1, CV_64FC3);
827 for( int i = 0; i < (int)objectPoints.total(); i++ )
828 {
829 tvecs.create(3, 1, CV_64F, i, true);
830 Mat tv = tvecs.getMat(i);
831 *tv.ptr<Vec3d>(0) = Tc[i];
832 }
833 }
834 else
835 {
836 cv::Mat(Tc).convertTo(tvecs, tvecs.fixedType() ? tvecs.type() : CV_64FC3);
837 }
838 }
839
840 return rms;
841}
842
843//////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
844/// cv::fisheye::stereoCalibrate
845
846double cv::fisheye::stereoCalibrate(InputArrayOfArrays objectPoints, InputArrayOfArrays imagePoints1, InputArrayOfArrays imagePoints2,
847 InputOutputArray K1, InputOutputArray D1, InputOutputArray K2, InputOutputArray D2, Size imageSize,
848 OutputArray R, OutputArray T, int flags, TermCriteria criteria)
849{
850 CV_Assert(!objectPoints.empty() && !imagePoints1.empty() && !imagePoints2.empty());
851 CV_Assert(objectPoints.total() == imagePoints1.total() || imagePoints1.total() == imagePoints2.total());
852 CV_Assert(objectPoints.type() == CV_32FC3 || objectPoints.type() == CV_64FC3);
853 CV_Assert(imagePoints1.type() == CV_32FC2 || imagePoints1.type() == CV_64FC2);
854 CV_Assert(imagePoints2.type() == CV_32FC2 || imagePoints2.type() == CV_64FC2);
855
856 CV_Assert((!K1.empty() && K1.size() == Size(3,3)) || K1.empty());
857 CV_Assert((!D1.empty() && D1.total() == 4) || D1.empty());
858 CV_Assert((!K2.empty() && K1.size() == Size(3,3)) || K2.empty());
859 CV_Assert((!D2.empty() && D1.total() == 4) || D2.empty());
860
861 CV_Assert(((flags & CALIB_FIX_INTRINSIC) && !K1.empty() && !K2.empty() && !D1.empty() && !D2.empty()) || !(flags & CALIB_FIX_INTRINSIC));
862
863 //-------------------------------Initialization
864
865 const int threshold = 50;
866 const double thresh_cond = 1e6;
867 const int check_cond = 1;
868
869 int n_points = (int)objectPoints.getMat(0).total();
870 int n_images = (int)objectPoints.total();
871
872 double change = 1;
873
874 cv::internal::IntrinsicParams intrinsicLeft;
875 cv::internal::IntrinsicParams intrinsicRight;
876
877 cv::internal::IntrinsicParams intrinsicLeft_errors;
878 cv::internal::IntrinsicParams intrinsicRight_errors;
879
880 Matx33d _K1, _K2;
881 Vec4d _D1, _D2;
882 if (!K1.empty()) K1.getMat().convertTo(_K1, CV_64FC1);
883 if (!D1.empty()) D1.getMat().convertTo(_D1, CV_64FC1);
884 if (!K2.empty()) K2.getMat().convertTo(_K2, CV_64FC1);
885 if (!D2.empty()) D2.getMat().convertTo(_D2, CV_64FC1);
886
887 std::vector<Vec3d> rvecs1(n_images), tvecs1(n_images), rvecs2(n_images), tvecs2(n_images);
888
889 if (!(flags & CALIB_FIX_INTRINSIC))
890 {
891 calibrate(objectPoints, imagePoints1, imageSize, _K1, _D1, rvecs1, tvecs1, flags, TermCriteria(3, 20, 1e-6));
892 calibrate(objectPoints, imagePoints2, imageSize, _K2, _D2, rvecs2, tvecs2, flags, TermCriteria(3, 20, 1e-6));
893 }
894
895 intrinsicLeft.Init(Vec2d(_K1(0,0), _K1(1, 1)), Vec2d(_K1(0,2), _K1(1, 2)),
896 Vec4d(_D1[0], _D1[1], _D1[2], _D1[3]), _K1(0, 1) / _K1(0, 0));
897
898 intrinsicRight.Init(Vec2d(_K2(0,0), _K2(1, 1)), Vec2d(_K2(0,2), _K2(1, 2)),
899 Vec4d(_D2[0], _D2[1], _D2[2], _D2[3]), _K2(0, 1) / _K2(0, 0));
900
901 if ((flags & CALIB_FIX_INTRINSIC))
902 {
903 internal::CalibrateExtrinsics(objectPoints, imagePoints1, intrinsicLeft, check_cond, thresh_cond, rvecs1, tvecs1);
904 internal::CalibrateExtrinsics(objectPoints, imagePoints2, intrinsicRight, check_cond, thresh_cond, rvecs2, tvecs2);
905 }
906
907 intrinsicLeft.isEstimate[0] = flags & CALIB_FIX_INTRINSIC ? 0 : 1;
908 intrinsicLeft.isEstimate[1] = flags & CALIB_FIX_INTRINSIC ? 0 : 1;
909 intrinsicLeft.isEstimate[2] = flags & CALIB_FIX_INTRINSIC ? 0 : 1;
910 intrinsicLeft.isEstimate[3] = flags & CALIB_FIX_INTRINSIC ? 0 : 1;
911 intrinsicLeft.isEstimate[4] = flags & (CALIB_FIX_SKEW | CALIB_FIX_INTRINSIC) ? 0 : 1;
912 intrinsicLeft.isEstimate[5] = flags & (CALIB_FIX_K1 | CALIB_FIX_INTRINSIC) ? 0 : 1;
913 intrinsicLeft.isEstimate[6] = flags & (CALIB_FIX_K2 | CALIB_FIX_INTRINSIC) ? 0 : 1;
914 intrinsicLeft.isEstimate[7] = flags & (CALIB_FIX_K3 | CALIB_FIX_INTRINSIC) ? 0 : 1;
915 intrinsicLeft.isEstimate[8] = flags & (CALIB_FIX_K4 | CALIB_FIX_INTRINSIC) ? 0 : 1;
916
917 intrinsicRight.isEstimate[0] = flags & CALIB_FIX_INTRINSIC ? 0 : 1;
918 intrinsicRight.isEstimate[1] = flags & CALIB_FIX_INTRINSIC ? 0 : 1;
919 intrinsicRight.isEstimate[2] = flags & CALIB_FIX_INTRINSIC ? 0 : 1;
920 intrinsicRight.isEstimate[3] = flags & CALIB_FIX_INTRINSIC ? 0 : 1;
921 intrinsicRight.isEstimate[4] = flags & (CALIB_FIX_SKEW | CALIB_FIX_INTRINSIC) ? 0 : 1;
922 intrinsicRight.isEstimate[5] = flags & (CALIB_FIX_K1 | CALIB_FIX_INTRINSIC) ? 0 : 1;
923 intrinsicRight.isEstimate[6] = flags & (CALIB_FIX_K2 | CALIB_FIX_INTRINSIC) ? 0 : 1;
924 intrinsicRight.isEstimate[7] = flags & (CALIB_FIX_K3 | CALIB_FIX_INTRINSIC) ? 0 : 1;
925 intrinsicRight.isEstimate[8] = flags & (CALIB_FIX_K4 | CALIB_FIX_INTRINSIC) ? 0 : 1;
926
927 intrinsicLeft_errors.isEstimate = intrinsicLeft.isEstimate;
928 intrinsicRight_errors.isEstimate = intrinsicRight.isEstimate;
929
930 std::vector<int> selectedParams;
931 std::vector<int> tmp(6 * (n_images + 1), 1);
932 selectedParams.insert(selectedParams.end(), intrinsicLeft.isEstimate.begin(), intrinsicLeft.isEstimate.end());
933 selectedParams.insert(selectedParams.end(), intrinsicRight.isEstimate.begin(), intrinsicRight.isEstimate.end());
934 selectedParams.insert(selectedParams.end(), tmp.begin(), tmp.end());
935
936 //Init values for rotation and translation between two views
937 cv::Mat om_list(1, n_images, CV_64FC3), T_list(1, n_images, CV_64FC3);
938 cv::Mat om_ref, R_ref, T_ref, R1, R2;
939 for (int image_idx = 0; image_idx < n_images; ++image_idx)
940 {
941 cv::Rodrigues(rvecs1[image_idx], R1);
942 cv::Rodrigues(rvecs2[image_idx], R2);
943 R_ref = R2 * R1.t();
944 T_ref = cv::Mat(tvecs2[image_idx]) - R_ref * cv::Mat(tvecs1[image_idx]);
945 cv::Rodrigues(R_ref, om_ref);
946 om_ref.reshape(3, 1).copyTo(om_list.col(image_idx));
947 T_ref.reshape(3, 1).copyTo(T_list.col(image_idx));
948 }
949 cv::Vec3d omcur = internal::median3d(om_list);
950 cv::Vec3d Tcur = internal::median3d(T_list);
951
952 cv::Mat J = cv::Mat::zeros(4 * n_points * n_images, 18 + 6 * (n_images + 1), CV_64FC1),
953 e = cv::Mat::zeros(4 * n_points * n_images, 1, CV_64FC1), Jkk, ekk;
954 cv::Mat J2_inv;
955
956 for(int iter = 0; ; ++iter)
957 {
958 if ((criteria.type == 1 && iter >= criteria.maxCount) ||
959 (criteria.type == 2 && change <= criteria.epsilon) ||
960 (criteria.type == 3 && (change <= criteria.epsilon || iter >= criteria.maxCount)))
961 break;
962
963 J.create(4 * n_points * n_images, 18 + 6 * (n_images + 1), CV_64FC1);
964 e.create(4 * n_points * n_images, 1, CV_64FC1);
965 Jkk.create(4 * n_points, 18 + 6 * (n_images + 1), CV_64FC1);
966 ekk.create(4 * n_points, 1, CV_64FC1);
967
968 cv::Mat omr, Tr, domrdomckk, domrdTckk, domrdom, domrdT, dTrdomckk, dTrdTckk, dTrdom, dTrdT;
969
970 for (int image_idx = 0; image_idx < n_images; ++image_idx)
971 {
972 Jkk = cv::Mat::zeros(4 * n_points, 18 + 6 * (n_images + 1), CV_64FC1);
973
974 cv::Mat object = objectPoints.getMat(image_idx).clone();
975 cv::Mat imageLeft = imagePoints1.getMat(image_idx).clone();
976 cv::Mat imageRight = imagePoints2.getMat(image_idx).clone();
977 cv::Mat jacobians, projected;
978
979 //left camera jacobian
980 cv::Mat rvec = cv::Mat(rvecs1[image_idx]);
981 cv::Mat tvec = cv::Mat(tvecs1[image_idx]);
982 cv::internal::projectPoints(object, projected, rvec, tvec, intrinsicLeft, jacobians);
983 cv::Mat(cv::Mat((imageLeft - projected).t()).reshape(1, 1).t()).copyTo(ekk.rowRange(0, 2 * n_points));
984 jacobians.colRange(8, 11).copyTo(Jkk.colRange(24 + image_idx * 6, 27 + image_idx * 6).rowRange(0, 2 * n_points));
985 jacobians.colRange(11, 14).copyTo(Jkk.colRange(27 + image_idx * 6, 30 + image_idx * 6).rowRange(0, 2 * n_points));
986 jacobians.colRange(0, 2).copyTo(Jkk.colRange(0, 2).rowRange(0, 2 * n_points));
987 jacobians.colRange(2, 4).copyTo(Jkk.colRange(2, 4).rowRange(0, 2 * n_points));
988 jacobians.colRange(4, 8).copyTo(Jkk.colRange(5, 9).rowRange(0, 2 * n_points));
989 jacobians.col(14).copyTo(Jkk.col(4).rowRange(0, 2 * n_points));
990
991 //right camera jacobian
992 internal::compose_motion(rvec, tvec, omcur, Tcur, omr, Tr, domrdomckk, domrdTckk, domrdom, domrdT, dTrdomckk, dTrdTckk, dTrdom, dTrdT);
993 rvec = cv::Mat(rvecs2[image_idx]);
994 tvec = cv::Mat(tvecs2[image_idx]);
995
996 cv::internal::projectPoints(object, projected, omr, Tr, intrinsicRight, jacobians);
997 cv::Mat(cv::Mat((imageRight - projected).t()).reshape(1, 1).t()).copyTo(ekk.rowRange(2 * n_points, 4 * n_points));
998 cv::Mat dxrdom = jacobians.colRange(8, 11) * domrdom + jacobians.colRange(11, 14) * dTrdom;
999 cv::Mat dxrdT = jacobians.colRange(8, 11) * domrdT + jacobians.colRange(11, 14)* dTrdT;
1000 cv::Mat dxrdomckk = jacobians.colRange(8, 11) * domrdomckk + jacobians.colRange(11, 14) * dTrdomckk;
1001 cv::Mat dxrdTckk = jacobians.colRange(8, 11) * domrdTckk + jacobians.colRange(11, 14) * dTrdTckk;
1002
1003 dxrdom.copyTo(Jkk.colRange(18, 21).rowRange(2 * n_points, 4 * n_points));
1004 dxrdT.copyTo(Jkk.colRange(21, 24).rowRange(2 * n_points, 4 * n_points));
1005 dxrdomckk.copyTo(Jkk.colRange(24 + image_idx * 6, 27 + image_idx * 6).rowRange(2 * n_points, 4 * n_points));
1006 dxrdTckk.copyTo(Jkk.colRange(27 + image_idx * 6, 30 + image_idx * 6).rowRange(2 * n_points, 4 * n_points));
1007 jacobians.colRange(0, 2).copyTo(Jkk.colRange(9 + 0, 9 + 2).rowRange(2 * n_points, 4 * n_points));
1008 jacobians.colRange(2, 4).copyTo(Jkk.colRange(9 + 2, 9 + 4).rowRange(2 * n_points, 4 * n_points));
1009 jacobians.colRange(4, 8).copyTo(Jkk.colRange(9 + 5, 9 + 9).rowRange(2 * n_points, 4 * n_points));
1010 jacobians.col(14).copyTo(Jkk.col(9 + 4).rowRange(2 * n_points, 4 * n_points));
1011
1012 //check goodness of sterepair
1013 double abs_max = 0;
1014 for (int i = 0; i < 4 * n_points; i++)
1015 {
1016 if (fabs(ekk.at<double>(i)) > abs_max)
1017 {
1018 abs_max = fabs(ekk.at<double>(i));
1019 }
1020 }
1021
1022 CV_Assert(abs_max < threshold); // bad stereo pair
1023
1024 Jkk.copyTo(J.rowRange(image_idx * 4 * n_points, (image_idx + 1) * 4 * n_points));
1025 ekk.copyTo(e.rowRange(image_idx * 4 * n_points, (image_idx + 1) * 4 * n_points));
1026 }
1027
1028 cv::Vec6d oldTom(Tcur[0], Tcur[1], Tcur[2], omcur[0], omcur[1], omcur[2]);
1029
1030 //update all parameters
1031 cv::subMatrix(J, J, selectedParams, std::vector<int>(J.rows, 1));
1032 cv::Mat J2 = J.t() * J;
1033 J2_inv = J2.inv();
1034 int a = cv::countNonZero(intrinsicLeft.isEstimate);
1035 int b = cv::countNonZero(intrinsicRight.isEstimate);
1036 cv::Mat deltas = J2_inv * J.t() * e;
1037 if (a > 0)
1038 intrinsicLeft = intrinsicLeft + deltas.rowRange(0, a);
1039 if (b > 0)
1040 intrinsicRight = intrinsicRight + deltas.rowRange(a, a + b);
1041 omcur = omcur + cv::Vec3d(deltas.rowRange(a + b, a + b + 3));
1042 Tcur = Tcur + cv::Vec3d(deltas.rowRange(a + b + 3, a + b + 6));
1043 for (int image_idx = 0; image_idx < n_images; ++image_idx)
1044 {
1045 rvecs1[image_idx] = cv::Mat(cv::Mat(rvecs1[image_idx]) + deltas.rowRange(a + b + 6 + image_idx * 6, a + b + 9 + image_idx * 6));
1046 tvecs1[image_idx] = cv::Mat(cv::Mat(tvecs1[image_idx]) + deltas.rowRange(a + b + 9 + image_idx * 6, a + b + 12 + image_idx * 6));
1047 }
1048
1049 cv::Vec6d newTom(Tcur[0], Tcur[1], Tcur[2], omcur[0], omcur[1], omcur[2]);
1050 change = cv::norm(newTom - oldTom) / cv::norm(newTom);
1051 }
1052
1053 double rms = 0;
1054 const Vec2d* ptr_e = e.ptr<Vec2d>();
1055 for (size_t i = 0; i < e.total() / 2; i++)
1056 {
1057 rms += ptr_e[i][0] * ptr_e[i][0] + ptr_e[i][1] * ptr_e[i][1];
1058 }
1059
1060 rms /= ((double)e.total() / 2.0);
1061 rms = sqrt(rms);
1062
1063 _K1 = Matx33d(intrinsicLeft.f[0], intrinsicLeft.f[0] * intrinsicLeft.alpha, intrinsicLeft.c[0],
1064 0, intrinsicLeft.f[1], intrinsicLeft.c[1],
1065 0, 0, 1);
1066
1067 _K2 = Matx33d(intrinsicRight.f[0], intrinsicRight.f[0] * intrinsicRight.alpha, intrinsicRight.c[0],
1068 0, intrinsicRight.f[1], intrinsicRight.c[1],
1069 0, 0, 1);
1070
1071 Mat _R;
1072 Rodrigues(omcur, _R);
1073
1074 if (K1.needed()) cv::Mat(_K1).convertTo(K1, K1.empty() ? CV_64FC1 : K1.type());
1075 if (K2.needed()) cv::Mat(_K2).convertTo(K2, K2.empty() ? CV_64FC1 : K2.type());
1076 if (D1.needed()) cv::Mat(intrinsicLeft.k).convertTo(D1, D1.empty() ? CV_64FC1 : D1.type());
1077 if (D2.needed()) cv::Mat(intrinsicRight.k).convertTo(D2, D2.empty() ? CV_64FC1 : D2.type());
1078 if (R.needed()) _R.convertTo(R, R.empty() ? CV_64FC1 : R.type());
1079 if (T.needed()) cv::Mat(Tcur).convertTo(T, T.empty() ? CV_64FC1 : T.type());
1080
1081 return rms;
1082}

1093 {

1097 }

1103 {

1111}

1185void cv::internal::ComputeExtrinsicRefine(const Mat& imagePoints, const Mat& objectPoints, Mat& rvec,
1186 Mat& tvec, Mat& J, const int MaxIter,
1187 const IntrinsicParams& param, const double thresh_cond)
1188{
1189 CV_Assert(!objectPoints.empty() && objectPoints.type() == CV_64FC3);
1190 CV_Assert(!imagePoints.empty() && imagePoints.type() == CV_64FC2);
1191 Vec6d extrinsics(rvec.at<double>(0), rvec.at<double>(1), rvec.at<double>(2),
1192 tvec.at<double>(0), tvec.at<double>(1), tvec.at<double>(2));
1193 double change = 1;
1194 int iter = 0;
1195
1196 while (change > 1e-10 && iter < MaxIter)
1197 {
1198 std::vector<Point2d> x;
1199 Mat jacobians;
1200 projectPoints(objectPoints, x, rvec, tvec, param, jacobians);
1201
1202 Mat ex = imagePoints - Mat(x).t();
1203 ex = ex.reshape(1, 2);
1204
1205 J = jacobians.colRange(8, 14).clone();
1206
1207 SVD svd(J, SVD::NO_UV);
1208 double condJJ = svd.w.at<double>(0)/svd.w.at<double>(5);
1209
1210 if (condJJ > thresh_cond)
1211 change = 0;
1212 else
1213 {
1214 Vec6d param_innov;
1215 solve(J, ex.reshape(1, (int)ex.total()), param_innov, DECOMP_SVD + DECOMP_NORMAL);
1216
1217 Vec6d param_up = extrinsics + param_innov;
1218 change = norm(param_innov)/norm(param_up);
1219 extrinsics = param_up;
1220 iter = iter + 1;
1221
1222 rvec = Mat(Vec3d(extrinsics.val));
1223 tvec = Mat(Vec3d(extrinsics.val+3));
1224 }
1225 }
1226}

1228cv::Mat cv::internal::ComputeHomography(Mat m, Mat M)
1229{
1230 int Np = m.cols;
1231
1232 if (m.rows < 3)
1233 {
1234 vconcat(m, Mat::ones(1, Np, CV_64FC1), m);
1235 }
1236 if (M.rows < 3)
1237 {
1238 vconcat(M, Mat::ones(1, Np, CV_64FC1), M);
1239 }
1240
1241 divide(m, Mat::ones(3, 1, CV_64FC1) * m.row(2), m);
1242 divide(M, Mat::ones(3, 1, CV_64FC1) * M.row(2), M);
1243
1244 Mat ax = m.row(0).clone();
1245 Mat ay = m.row(1).clone();
1246
1247 double mxx = mean(ax)[0];
1248 double myy = mean(ay)[0];
1249
1250 ax = ax - mxx;
1251 ay = ay - myy;
1252
1253 double scxx = mean(abs(ax))[0];
1254 double scyy = mean(abs(ay))[0];
1255
1256 Mat Hnorm (Matx33d( 1/scxx, 0.0, -mxx/scxx,
1257 0.0, 1/scyy, -myy/scyy,
1258 0.0, 0.0, 1.0 ));
1259
1260 Mat inv_Hnorm (Matx33d( scxx, 0, mxx,
1261 0, scyy, myy,
1262 0, 0, 1 ));
1263 Mat mn = Hnorm * m;
1264
1265 Mat L = Mat::zeros(2*Np, 9, CV_64FC1);
1266
1267 for (int i = 0; i < Np; ++i)
1268 {
1269 for (int j = 0; j < 3; j++)
1270 {
1271 L.at<double>(2 * i, j) = M.at<double>(j, i);
1272 L.at<double>(2 * i + 1, j + 3) = M.at<double>(j, i);
1273 L.at<double>(2 * i, j + 6) = -mn.at<double>(0,i) * M.at<double>(j, i);
1274 L.at<double>(2 * i + 1, j + 6) = -mn.at<double>(1,i) * M.at<double>(j, i);
1275 }
1276 }
1277
1278 if (Np > 4) L = L.t() * L;
1279 SVD svd(L);
1280 Mat hh = svd.vt.row(8) / svd.vt.row(8).at<double>(8);
1281 Mat Hrem = hh.reshape(1, 3);
1282 Mat H = inv_Hnorm * Hrem;
1283
1284 if (Np > 4)
1285 {
1286 Mat hhv = H.reshape(1, 9)(Rect(0, 0, 1, 8)).clone();
1287 for (int iter = 0; iter < 10; iter++)
1288 {
1289 Mat mrep = H * M;
1290 Mat J = Mat::zeros(2 * Np, 8, CV_64FC1);
1291 Mat MMM;
1292 divide(M, Mat::ones(3, 1, CV_64FC1) * mrep(Rect(0, 2, mrep.cols, 1)), MMM);
1293 divide(mrep, Mat::ones(3, 1, CV_64FC1) * mrep(Rect(0, 2, mrep.cols, 1)), mrep);
1294 Mat m_err = m(Rect(0,0, m.cols, 2)) - mrep(Rect(0,0, mrep.cols, 2));
1295 m_err = Mat(m_err.t()).reshape(1, m_err.cols * m_err.rows);
1296 Mat MMM2, MMM3;
1297 multiply(Mat::ones(3, 1, CV_64FC1) * mrep(Rect(0, 0, mrep.cols, 1)), MMM, MMM2);
1298 multiply(Mat::ones(3, 1, CV_64FC1) * mrep(Rect(0, 1, mrep.cols, 1)), MMM, MMM3);
1299
1300 for (int i = 0; i < Np; ++i)
1301 {
1302 for (int j = 0; j < 3; ++j)
1303 {
1304 J.at<double>(2 * i, j) = -MMM.at<double>(j, i);
1305 J.at<double>(2 * i + 1, j + 3) = -MMM.at<double>(j, i);
1306 }
1307
1308 for (int j = 0; j < 2; ++j)
1309 {
1310 J.at<double>(2 * i, j + 6) = MMM2.at<double>(j, i);
1311 J.at<double>(2 * i + 1, j + 6) = MMM3.at<double>(j, i);
1312 }
1313 }
1314 divide(M, Mat::ones(3, 1, CV_64FC1) * mrep(Rect(0,2,mrep.cols,1)), MMM);
1315 Mat hh_innov = (J.t() * J).inv() * (J.t()) * m_err;
1316 Mat hhv_up = hhv - hh_innov;
1317 Mat tmp;
1318 vconcat(hhv_up, Mat::ones(1,1,CV_64FC1), tmp);
1319 Mat H_up = tmp.reshape(1,3);
1320 hhv = hhv_up;
1321 H = H_up;
1322 }
1323 }
1324 return H;
1325}

1327cv::Mat cv::internal::NormalizePixels(const Mat& imagePoints, const IntrinsicParams& param)
1328{
1329 CV_Assert(!imagePoints.empty() && imagePoints.type() == CV_64FC2);
1330
1331 Mat distorted((int)imagePoints.total(), 1, CV_64FC2), undistorted;
1332 const Vec2d* ptr = imagePoints.ptr<Vec2d>(0);
1333 Vec2d* ptr_d = distorted.ptr<Vec2d>(0);
1334 for (size_t i = 0; i < imagePoints.total(); ++i)
1335 {
1336 ptr_d[i] = (ptr[i] - param.c).mul(Vec2d(1.0 / param.f[0], 1.0 / param.f[1]));
1337 ptr_d[i][0] = ptr_d[i][0] - param.alpha * ptr_d[i][1];
1338 }
1339 cv::fisheye::undistortPoints(distorted, undistorted, Matx33d::eye(), param.k);
1340 return undistorted;
1341}

1343void cv::internal::InitExtrinsics(const Mat& _imagePoints, const Mat& _objectPoints, const IntrinsicParams& param, Mat& omckk, Mat& Tckk)
1344{
1345
1346 CV_Assert(!_objectPoints.empty() && _objectPoints.type() == CV_64FC3);
1347 CV_Assert(!_imagePoints.empty() && _imagePoints.type() == CV_64FC2);
1348
1349 Mat imagePointsNormalized = NormalizePixels(_imagePoints.t(), param).reshape(1).t();
1350 Mat objectPoints = Mat(_objectPoints.t()).reshape(1).t();
1351 Mat objectPointsMean, covObjectPoints;
1352 Mat Rckk;
1353 int Np = imagePointsNormalized.cols;
1354 calcCovarMatrix(objectPoints, covObjectPoints, objectPointsMean, CV_COVAR_NORMAL | CV_COVAR_COLS);
1355 SVD svd(covObjectPoints);
1356 Mat R(svd.vt);
1357 if (norm(R(Rect(2, 0, 1, 2))) < 1e-6)
1358 R = Mat::eye(3,3, CV_64FC1);
1359 if (determinant(R) < 0)
1360 R = -R;
1361 Mat T = -R * objectPointsMean;
1362 Mat X_new = R * objectPoints + T * Mat::ones(1, Np, CV_64FC1);
1363 Mat H = ComputeHomography(imagePointsNormalized, X_new(Rect(0,0,X_new.cols,2)));
1364 double sc = .5 * (norm(H.col(0)) + norm(H.col(1)));
1365 H = H / sc;
1366 Mat u1 = H.col(0).clone();
1367 u1 = u1 / norm(u1);
1368 Mat u2 = H.col(1).clone() - u1.dot(H.col(1).clone()) * u1;
1369 u2 = u2 / norm(u2);
1370 Mat u3 = u1.cross(u2);
1371 Mat RRR;
1372 hconcat(u1, u2, RRR);
1373 hconcat(RRR, u3, RRR);
1374 Rodrigues(RRR, omckk);
1375 Rodrigues(omckk, Rckk);
1376 Tckk = H.col(2).clone();
1377 Tckk = Tckk + Rckk * T;
1378 Rckk = Rckk * R;
1379 Rodrigues(Rckk, omckk);
1380}

1382void cv::internal::CalibrateExtrinsics(InputArrayOfArrays objectPoints, InputArrayOfArrays imagePoints,
1383 const IntrinsicParams& param, const int check_cond,
1384 const double thresh_cond, InputOutputArray omc, InputOutputArray Tc)
1385{
1386 CV_Assert(!objectPoints.empty() && (objectPoints.type() == CV_32FC3 || objectPoints.type() == CV_64FC3));
1387 CV_Assert(!imagePoints.empty() && (imagePoints.type() == CV_32FC2 || imagePoints.type() == CV_64FC2));
1388 CV_Assert(omc.type() == CV_64FC3 || Tc.type() == CV_64FC3);
1389
1390 if (omc.empty()) omc.create(1, (int)objectPoints.total(), CV_64FC3);
1391 if (Tc.empty()) Tc.create(1, (int)objectPoints.total(), CV_64FC3);
1392
1393 const int maxIter = 20;
1394
1395 for(int image_idx = 0; image_idx < (int)imagePoints.total(); ++image_idx)
1396 {
1397 Mat omckk, Tckk, JJ_kk;
1398 Mat image, object;
1399
1400 objectPoints.getMat(image_idx).convertTo(object, CV_64FC3);
1401 imagePoints.getMat (image_idx).convertTo(image, CV_64FC2);
1402
1403 InitExtrinsics(image, object, param, omckk, Tckk);
1404
1405 ComputeExtrinsicRefine(image, object, omckk, Tckk, JJ_kk, maxIter, param, thresh_cond);
1406 if (check_cond)
1407 {
1408 SVD svd(JJ_kk, SVD::NO_UV);
1409 CV_Assert(svd.w.at<double>(0) / svd.w.at<double>((int)svd.w.total() - 1) < thresh_cond);
1410 }
1411 omckk.reshape(3,1).copyTo(omc.getMat().col(image_idx));
1412 Tckk.reshape(3,1).copyTo(Tc.getMat().col(image_idx));
1413 }
1414}

1416
1417void cv::internal::ComputeJacobians(InputArrayOfArrays objectPoints, InputArrayOfArrays imagePoints,
1418 const IntrinsicParams& param, InputArray omc, InputArray Tc,
1419 const int& check_cond, const double& thresh_cond, Mat& JJ2_inv, Mat& ex3)
1420{
1421 CV_Assert(!objectPoints.empty() && (objectPoints.type() == CV_32FC3 || objectPoints.type() == CV_64FC3));
1422 CV_Assert(!imagePoints.empty() && (imagePoints.type() == CV_32FC2 || imagePoints.type() == CV_64FC2));
1423
1424 CV_Assert(!omc.empty() && omc.type() == CV_64FC3);
1425 CV_Assert(!Tc.empty() && Tc.type() == CV_64FC3);
1426
1427 int n = (int)objectPoints.total();
1428
1429 Mat JJ3 = Mat::zeros(9 + 6 * n, 9 + 6 * n, CV_64FC1);
1430 ex3 = Mat::zeros(9 + 6 * n, 1, CV_64FC1 );
1431
1432 for (int image_idx = 0; image_idx < n; ++image_idx)
1433 {
1434 Mat image, object;
1435 objectPoints.getMat(image_idx).convertTo(object, CV_64FC3);
1436 imagePoints.getMat (image_idx).convertTo(image, CV_64FC2);
1437
1438 Mat om(omc.getMat().col(image_idx)), T(Tc.getMat().col(image_idx));
1439
1440 std::vector<Point2d> x;
1441 Mat jacobians;
1442 projectPoints(object, x, om, T, param, jacobians);
1443 Mat exkk = image.t() - Mat(x);
1444
1445 Mat A(jacobians.rows, 9, CV_64FC1);
1446 jacobians.colRange(0, 4).copyTo(A.colRange(0, 4));
1447 jacobians.col(14).copyTo(A.col(4));
1448 jacobians.colRange(4, 8).copyTo(A.colRange(5, 9));
1449
1450 A = A.t();
1451
1452 Mat B = jacobians.colRange(8, 14).clone();
1453 B = B.t();
1454
1455 JJ3(Rect(0, 0, 9, 9)) = JJ3(Rect(0, 0, 9, 9)) + A * A.t();
1456 JJ3(Rect(9 + 6 * image_idx, 9 + 6 * image_idx, 6, 6)) = B * B.t();
1457
1458 Mat AB = A * B.t();
1459 AB.copyTo(JJ3(Rect(9 + 6 * image_idx, 0, 6, 9)));
1460
1461 JJ3(Rect(0, 9 + 6 * image_idx, 9, 6)) = AB.t();
1462 ex3(Rect(0,0,1,9)) = ex3(Rect(0,0,1,9)) + A * exkk.reshape(1, 2 * exkk.rows);
1463
1464 ex3(Rect(0, 9 + 6 * image_idx, 1, 6)) = B * exkk.reshape(1, 2 * exkk.rows);
1465
1466 if (check_cond)
1467 {
1468 Mat JJ_kk = B.t();
1469 SVD svd(JJ_kk, SVD::NO_UV);
1470 CV_Assert(svd.w.at<double>(0) / svd.w.at<double>(svd.w.rows - 1) < thresh_cond);
1471 }
1472 }
1473
1474 vector<int> idxs(param.isEstimate);
1475 idxs.insert(idxs.end(), 6 * n, 1);
1476
1477 subMatrix(JJ3, JJ3, idxs, idxs);
1478 subMatrix(ex3, ex3, std::vector<int>(1, 1), idxs);
1479 JJ2_inv = JJ3.inv();
1480}

1482void cv::internal::EstimateUncertainties(InputArrayOfArrays objectPoints, InputArrayOfArrays imagePoints,
1483 const IntrinsicParams& params, InputArray omc, InputArray Tc,
1484 IntrinsicParams& errors, Vec2d& std_err, double thresh_cond, int check_cond, double& rms)
1485{
1486 CV_Assert(!objectPoints.empty() && (objectPoints.type() == CV_32FC3 || objectPoints.type() == CV_64FC3));
1487 CV_Assert(!imagePoints.empty() && (imagePoints.type() == CV_32FC2 || imagePoints.type() == CV_64FC2));
1488
1489 CV_Assert(!omc.empty() && omc.type() == CV_64FC3);
1490 CV_Assert(!Tc.empty() && Tc.type() == CV_64FC3);
1491
1492 Mat ex((int)(objectPoints.getMat(0).total() * objectPoints.total()), 1, CV_64FC2);
1493
1494 for (int image_idx = 0; image_idx < (int)objectPoints.total(); ++image_idx)
1495 {
1496 Mat image, object;
1497 objectPoints.getMat(image_idx).convertTo(object, CV_64FC3);
1498 imagePoints.getMat (image_idx).convertTo(image, CV_64FC2);
1499
1500 Mat om(omc.getMat().col(image_idx)), T(Tc.getMat().col(image_idx));
1501
1502 std::vector<Point2d> x;
1503 projectPoints(object, x, om, T, params, noArray());
1504 Mat ex_ = image.t() - Mat(x);
1505 ex_.copyTo(ex.rowRange(ex_.rows * image_idx, ex_.rows * (image_idx + 1)));
1506 }
1507
1508 meanStdDev(ex, noArray(), std_err);
1509 std_err *= sqrt((double)ex.total()/((double)ex.total() - 1.0));
1510
1511 Mat sigma_x;
1512 meanStdDev(ex.reshape(1, 1), noArray(), sigma_x);
1513 sigma_x *= sqrt(2.0 * (double)ex.total()/(2.0 * (double)ex.total() - 1.0));
1514
1515 Mat _JJ2_inv, ex3;
1516 ComputeJacobians(objectPoints, imagePoints, params, omc, Tc, check_cond, thresh_cond, _JJ2_inv, ex3);
1517
1518 Mat_<double>& JJ2_inv = (Mat_<double>&)_JJ2_inv;
1519
1520 sqrt(JJ2_inv, JJ2_inv);
1521
1522 double s = sigma_x.at<double>(0);
1523 Mat r = 3 * s * JJ2_inv.diag();
1524 errors = r;
1525
1526 rms = 0;
1527 const Vec2d* ptr_ex = ex.ptr<Vec2d>();
1528 for (size_t i = 0; i < ex.total(); i++)
1529 {
1530 rms += ptr_ex[i][0] * ptr_ex[i][0] + ptr_ex[i][1] * ptr_ex[i][1];
1531 }
1532
1533 rms /= (double)ex.total();
1534 rms = sqrt(rms);
1535}

1537void cv::internal::dAB(InputArray A, InputArray B, OutputArray dABdA, OutputArray dABdB)
1538{
1539 CV_Assert(A.getMat().cols == B.getMat().rows);
1540 CV_Assert(A.type() == CV_64FC1 && B.type() == CV_64FC1);
1541
1542 int p = A.getMat().rows;
1543 int n = A.getMat().cols;
1544 int q = B.getMat().cols;
1545
1546 dABdA.create(p * q, p * n, CV_64FC1);
1547 dABdB.create(p * q, q * n, CV_64FC1);
1548
1549 dABdA.getMat() = Mat::zeros(p * q, p * n, CV_64FC1);
1550 dABdB.getMat() = Mat::zeros(p * q, q * n, CV_64FC1);
1551
1552 for (int i = 0; i < q; ++i)
1553 {
1554 for (int j = 0; j < p; ++j)
1555 {
1556 int ij = j + i * p;
1557 for (int k = 0; k < n; ++k)
1558 {
1559 int kj = j + k * p;
1560 dABdA.getMat().at<double>(ij, kj) = B.getMat().at<double>(k, i);
1561 }
1562 }
1563 }
1564
1565 for (int i = 0; i < q; ++i)
1566 {
1567 A.getMat().copyTo(dABdB.getMat().rowRange(i * p, i * p + p).colRange(i * n, i * n + n));
1568 }
1569}

1571void cv::internal::JRodriguesMatlab(const Mat& src, Mat& dst)
1572{
1573 Mat tmp(src.cols, src.rows, src.type());
1574 if (src.rows == 9)
1575 {
1576 Mat(src.row(0).t()).copyTo(tmp.col(0));
1577 Mat(src.row(1).t()).copyTo(tmp.col(3));
1578 Mat(src.row(2).t()).copyTo(tmp.col(6));
1579 Mat(src.row(3).t()).copyTo(tmp.col(1));
1580 Mat(src.row(4).t()).copyTo(tmp.col(4));
1581 Mat(src.row(5).t()).copyTo(tmp.col(7));
1582 Mat(src.row(6).t()).copyTo(tmp.col(2));
1583 Mat(src.row(7).t()).copyTo(tmp.col(5));
1584 Mat(src.row(8).t()).copyTo(tmp.col(8));
1585 }
1586 else
1587 {
1588 Mat(src.col(0).t()).copyTo(tmp.row(0));
1589 Mat(src.col(1).t()).copyTo(tmp.row(3));
1590 Mat(src.col(2).t()).copyTo(tmp.row(6));
1591 Mat(src.col(3).t()).copyTo(tmp.row(1));
1592 Mat(src.col(4).t()).copyTo(tmp.row(4));
1593 Mat(src.col(5).t()).copyTo(tmp.row(7));
1594 Mat(src.col(6).t()).copyTo(tmp.row(2));
1595 Mat(src.col(7).t()).copyTo(tmp.row(5));
1596 Mat(src.col(8).t()).copyTo(tmp.row(8));
1597 }
1598 dst = tmp.clone();
1599}

1601void cv::internal::compose_motion(InputArray _om1, InputArray _T1, InputArray _om2, InputArray _T2,
1602 Mat& om3, Mat& T3, Mat& dom3dom1, Mat& dom3dT1, Mat& dom3dom2,
1603 Mat& dom3dT2, Mat& dT3dom1, Mat& dT3dT1, Mat& dT3dom2, Mat& dT3dT2)
1604{
1605 Mat om1 = _om1.getMat();
1606 Mat om2 = _om2.getMat();
1607 Mat T1 = _T1.getMat().reshape(1, 3);
1608 Mat T2 = _T2.getMat().reshape(1, 3);
1609
1610 //% Rotations:
1611 Mat R1, R2, R3, dR1dom1(9, 3, CV_64FC1), dR2dom2;
1612 Rodrigues(om1, R1, dR1dom1);
1613 Rodrigues(om2, R2, dR2dom2);
1614 JRodriguesMatlab(dR1dom1, dR1dom1);
1615 JRodriguesMatlab(dR2dom2, dR2dom2);
1616 R3 = R2 * R1;
1617 Mat dR3dR2, dR3dR1;
1618 dAB(R2, R1, dR3dR2, dR3dR1);
1619 Mat dom3dR3;
1620 Rodrigues(R3, om3, dom3dR3);
1621 JRodriguesMatlab(dom3dR3, dom3dR3);
1622 dom3dom1 = dom3dR3 * dR3dR1 * dR1dom1;
1623 dom3dom2 = dom3dR3 * dR3dR2 * dR2dom2;
1624 dom3dT1 = Mat::zeros(3, 3, CV_64FC1);
1625 dom3dT2 = Mat::zeros(3, 3, CV_64FC1);
1626
1627 //% Translations:
1628 Mat T3t = R2 * T1;
1629 Mat dT3tdR2, dT3tdT1;
1630 dAB(R2, T1, dT3tdR2, dT3tdT1);
1631 Mat dT3tdom2 = dT3tdR2 * dR2dom2;
1632 T3 = T3t + T2;
1633 dT3dT1 = dT3tdT1;
1634 dT3dT2 = Mat::eye(3, 3, CV_64FC1);
1635 dT3dom2 = dT3tdom2;
1636 dT3dom1 = Mat::zeros(3, 3, CV_64FC1);
1637}

1639double cv::internal::median(const Mat& row)
1640{
1641 CV_Assert(row.type() == CV_64FC1);
1642 CV_Assert(!row.empty() && row.rows == 1);
1643 Mat tmp = row.clone();
1644 sort(tmp, tmp, 0);
1645 if ((int)tmp.total() % 2) return tmp.at<double>((int)tmp.total() / 2);
1646 else return 0.5 *(tmp.at<double>((int)tmp.total() / 2) + tmp.at<double>((int)tmp.total() / 2 - 1));
1647}

1649cv::Vec3d cv::internal::median3d(InputArray m)
1650{
1651 CV_Assert(m.depth() == CV_64F && m.getMat().rows == 1);
1652 Mat M = Mat(m.getMat().t()).reshape(1).t();
1653 return Vec3d(median(M.row(0)), median(M.row(1)), median(M.row(2)));
1654}
